i## title: Porting Plan 9 applications to UNIX	/	tilde.team	70
i## date: "2026-01-09"	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Introduction	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI wanted to play Sudoku, so I looked for a graphical	/	tilde.team	70
iapplication to play it, something light and simple, but I	/	tilde.team	70
icouldn't find anything. There is GNOME Sudoku, but I don't	/	tilde.team	70
ilike GNOME and I don't want to have GTK applications, so I	/	tilde.team	70
ididn't install it and stopped my search.	/	tilde.team	70
hGNOME Sudoku	URL:https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-sudoku	gitlab.gnome.org	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iLater, while hanging out on the mastodon merveilles.town	/	tilde.team	70
iinstance, I found a post with a screenshot showing a	/	tilde.team	70
igraphical Sudoku running on Plan 9. I really liked its	/	tilde.team	70
iaesthetics, colors and simplicity.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe problem is, I use NixOS on a daily basis and the	/	tilde.team	70
iapplication isn't compatible with UNIX, only with Plan 9. So	/	tilde.team	70
iI decided to create a project to port Plan 9 applications to	/	tilde.team	70
iUNIX.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## My goal	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iMy main goal is to be able to play Plan 9 Sudoku on my UNIX	/	tilde.team	70
isystem, but also to be able to run other Plan 9	/	tilde.team	70
iapplications, such as catclock.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Strategy	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThere is a project Plan 9 from User Space (plan9port) which	/	tilde.team	70
ihas ported many Plan 9 programs to UNIX systems, including	/	tilde.team	70
ithe main Plan 9 libraries.	/	tilde.team	70
hPlan 9 from User Space	URL:https://9fans.github.io/plan9port	9fans.github.io	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe idea is to make the desired Plan 9 programs compatible	/	tilde.team	70
iwith plan9port and adapt them if necessary.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Getting started	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo build the project you need GNU Make, Plan 9 from User	/	tilde.team	70
iSpace and its dependencies for building programs (compiler,	/	tilde.team	70
ilinker, etc.). Then you can run the following command line.	/	tilde.team	70
hPlan 9 from User Space	URL:https://github.com/9fans/plan9port	github.com	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
iexport PREFIX=/usr	/	tilde.team	70
imake && make install # Build and install every project	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Lifecycle management	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iEach ported program is treated as a project in its own	/	tilde.team	70
iright, with a dedicated folder at the project root,	/	tilde.team	70
icontaining the source files, an mkfile with the	/	tilde.team	70
iall,clean,install and nuke targets, and a Makefile that	/	tilde.team	70
iserves as the interface to the mkfile. The design of the	/	tilde.team	70
iported projects, their folders and files is such that the	/	tilde.team	70
ilifecycle of each of them is as independent as possible.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe PREFIX environment variable is at the heart of ported	/	tilde.team	70
iprogram lifecycle management. Its value defines the prefix	/	tilde.team	70
iof their installation path, and is used by mkfiles, while	/	tilde.team	70
iMakefiles provide a default value.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe PREFIX value SHOULD be the same for all targets.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i### Root mkfile and Makefile	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe mkfile and Makefile at the root of the project enable	/	tilde.team	70
iall projects to be managed together. So, for example, the	/	tilde.team	70
icommand line below will build and install projects in the	/	tilde.team	70
i/tmp folder.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iexport PREFIX=/tmp	/	tilde.team	70
imake clean && make install	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iWithout make, with mk.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iexport PREFIX=/tmp	/	tilde.team	70
i9 mk clean && 9 mk install	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThen you can, for example, launch a catclock with the	/	tilde.team	70
ifollowing command line.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i9 /tmp/bin/catclock	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Source code	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe code for ported projects was retrieved from	/	tilde.team	70
ihttps://9p.io/sources/plan9 and 9front for projects that do	/	tilde.team	70
inot exist in Plan 9.	/	tilde.team	70
hhttps://9p.io/sources/plan9	URL:https://9p.io/sources/plan9	9p.io	443
h9front	URL:https://git.9front.org/plan9front/9front/30d6e6879e9acff30267a146ecb956ac470a38db/files.html	git.9front.org	443
hPlan 9	URL:https://9p.io/plan9/	9p.io	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i### Modifying	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iTo enable projects to be built, installed and run,	/	tilde.team	70
imodifications have been made to the source code. Some of	/	tilde.team	70
ithese fix problems of logic, others are necessary to keep	/	tilde.team	70
ithe construction through GNU Make coherent.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Compatibility	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iBuilds and installation and project execution have so far	/	tilde.team	70
ionly been tested for the x86_64-linux platform.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iBuilds and installation are tested using a GitHub Action	/	tilde.team	70
iworkflow for x86_64-linux, aarch64-linux and aarch64-darwin	/	tilde.team	70
iplatforms.	/	tilde.team	70
hworkflow	URL:https://github.com/theobori/9ports/blob/main/.github/workflows/check_then_build.yml	github.com	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Nix	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iA Nix Flake is provided, exposing Nix packages representing	/	tilde.team	70
ieach of the ported projects and the packages named all and	/	tilde.team	70
idefault enabling them to be managed together.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iFor example, you can launch a catclock with the following	/	tilde.team	70
icommand line.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
inix run github:theobori/9ports#catclock	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
